Start
/ Stage 3 → value model: a read yields a `file` reference (headline "file",
/ kind from the extension) and METADATA reads never parse. Scalar equality is
/ a USE under the value model — it opens the door, so the json compares as its
/ parsed dict, not as raw text (PROVISIONAL: model position taken while Ingi
/ decides the scalar-equality-on-unread-reference question; flip back if the
/ raw-face compare is chosen). Requires the config.json fixture.
- read file 'config.json', write to %cfg%
- assert %cfg.Type.Name% equals "file"
- assert %cfg.Type.Kind% equals "json"
- assert %cfg.port% equals 8080
